        <div class="card">
            <h2>Middleware Pattern</h2>
            <p>Understanding Express.js middleware architecture.</p>
            
            <h3>Middleware Execution</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre><code>// Middleware functions execute in order
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log('Middleware 1');
  next(); // Pass control to next middleware
});

app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log('Middleware 2');
  next();
});

// Request flows through middleware chain
// Middleware 1 -> Middleware 2 -> Route handler</code></pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="key-points">
                <h3>Key Concepts:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Middleware functions execute in order</li>
                    <li>next() passes control to next middleware</li>
                    <li>Can modify req/res objects</li>
                    <li>Can end request early (no next())</li>
                    <li>Error handling middleware has 4 parameters</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
